<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1913-02-09T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1913-02-09T00:00:00-05:00" n="1645" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d1645">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 816.001Ar1/2.</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">American Minister</gloss> to
                                the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>.</hi>
                        </head>
                        <opener>
                            <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.]</seg>
                        </opener>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">American Legation</hi>, <lb/>
                                    <hi rend="italic">San Salvador</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1913-02-09">
                                    <hi rend="italic">February 9, 1913</hi></date>.</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>President Araújo died at half past four o’clock this afternoon. The
                            Presidential Power has been vested in Señor Carlos Meléndez, the First
                            Substitute.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Heimke</hi>.</signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>